- **Finding 1 (HIGH)**: All four `chat-panel-*-chromium-linux.png` snapshots updated by this PR are byte-identical to each other (one git blob `89f7f1d…` for all four files) and visually depict the **daily briefing dashboard**, not the chat panel — so the new desktop pills have no automated visual evidence. Root cause: the test locator `page.locator('div.flex-1.flex.flex-col').first()` in `frontend/e2e/visual.spec.ts:362,374` selects the briefing panel on desktop. Two of the four PNGs (`chat-panel-empty-dark-…`, `chat-panel-with-messages-dark-…`) are also orphans — no test in `visual.spec.ts` produces them. This violates CLAUDE.md's "screenshots are the visual contract" rule despite `implementation.md` claiming a clean visual inspection. Recommended fix: add `data-testid="chat-panel"` to ChatPanel's root, switch the two tests to `page.getByTestId('chat-panel')`, delete the two orphan `-dark` PNGs, regenerate.

- **Finding 2 (LOW)**: `shrink-0` on the new desktop pill buttons is a no-op under `flex-wrap` (copy-pasted from the mobile `overflow-x-auto` block). Cosmetic only — fold into the Finding 1 follow-up.

**CLAUDE.md compliance**: All rules pass except the "visually inspect every updated PNG" step, which fails as documented in Finding 1.
